Project MED.BAT: Mission: care for wounded servicemen of the Russian Army; providing competent assistance to medical personnel in medical institutions where military personnel of the Russian Defense Ministry are being treated. Do they pay for volunteering: NO, but we pay for: - training,;
- obtaining documents required for admission to institutions;
- accommodation during training;
- purchasing MED.BAT protective clothing. Where to start: - go to the bot@medbat_svr_fond_bot, write your data;
- you are contacted and invited to a general meeting;
- a “platoon” is completed - 30 people;
- a contact is signed, according to which you study at the expense of the fund and commit to volunteering at the hospital. If you refuse to fulfill contractual obligations, you will reimburse the costs incurred;
- you purchase tickets and go to the place of training;
- training lasts 9 days, including practice in traumatology and surgery;
- after receiving your diploma, you are assigned to a hospital and, according to a schedule agreed with you, go out to serve. Is it dangerous to volunteer at MED.BATH:
- no! Business trips to LBS pose a danger. But they will be carried out exclusively by those volunteers who decide this of their own free will. When the assembly and start of training: - as the “1st platoon” is recruited, tentatively April 15th.
If there is a delay, then on April 22, 2024, they will be sent for training to the MED.BATA Center.

