FSIN employees will soon be forced to be used in war. 8 senators and 16 deputies associated with the Presidential Administration introduced a bill to the State Duma (Andrei Turchak, Maria Butina, etc.), directly supervised by the Putin administration. The draft Federal Law determines that in conditions of martial law, counter-terrorism operations and during war, FSIN employees will, without their consent:
- travel to another location;

- assign additional responsibilities to them;

- transfer to other units while maintaining the nature of the service;

- establish other conditions and restrictions.

The bill also provides for the conclusion of short-term contracts with the Federal Penitentiary Service for work in special conditions. In addition, the age limit for service is being lifted.

The Government of the Russian Federation has already supported this bill, which indicates the coordination of the actions of the initiators of this bill. A Gulagu net source in the State Duma reported on a meeting between Volodin and faction leaders, where he officially, after agreement with the Presidential Administration, stated that the law would be adopted in the spring session and signed by Putin by the end of May and must be supported unanimously.

One of the FSIN employees who left Russia with the support of Gulagu net commented on this initiative of the authorities: “The lafa is over, if previously the above was only in contracts, now in the form of a separate regulatory act. I believe that there will be orders, as when sent to the illegal armed group Wagner ", only now they will send employees. Surely this bill will be adopted quickly."

